
### This is a list of packages I regularly use
### Not all of them are required, to get my configs to work
### The sole purpose of this list, is to make a reinstallation of my system easier



### Special Characters:

"" Quotes imply, that the name stated is not the actual name of the package, but rather a name of the program. This is because some programs require a more complex installation progress (eg nvidia drivers)

() Parenthesis imply, that a package is optional. I dont use it, but still prefer it being installed on my system

* An Asterisk implies a subcategory of dependencies, to get my config to work





